  "text": "(Ω) with s ∈ R denote the potential Sobolev spaces based in L 2 ; W 2,∞ (Ω) stands for the Sobolev space with two derivaties in L ∞ ; B s (∂Ω) with 0 < |s| < 1 denotes the Besov spaces B s p,q (∂Ω) with p = q = 2. A quite complete description of these spaces can be found in [CITATION_1] .",
